Examine your favorite animes and manga and see what makes them so good (but don't steal ideas). Then finally, start drawing. <p><b>NieA loves you.</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspike0909.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spike0909</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/11/02 2:17:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1850.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Need Help With Manga Strip! Just Some Tips.</span><hr size=1> Well I guess everyone's pretty much correct but I'll have to say that in terms of art style you ditch the whole 'looking at other comics' to see how other artists do things.<br>
It's best to take down notes then move the art from in front of you completely whenever you draw. Helps you to create your own style and be original. If you're trying to copy someone you'll find drawing your characters is very difficult unless you're looking at sample art done by someone you're emulating.<br>
For an even more original style you should try to draw the thing as realistically as you possibly can. That's not manga but wait...you'd realise that manga art takes out certain lines and such from a character especially in the faces of the characters. This is because manga artists simplify their realistic style to generate super cool art. They simplify it and emphasis certain things to make the art more unique and cooler(whether it be hands,feet,eyes, slight muscle alterations or whatnot).<br>
If you're really serious about creating something of quality then you'd buy a few drawing books and I mean ones on anatomy not &quot;How to Draw Manga&quot; because those usually suck.<br>
Well all that's just what I think about when I draw comics myself. It's pretty obvious too I mean look at Akira...how'd you think he could do such detailed cities and mecha? The guy was a mechanical engineer...this stuff takes time and practice. This is a good site to help you along the way.<br>
Another thing I think about is storytelling by panelling. I draw out my pages without the word balloons at all and if my panels and the drawings within them cannot tell at least part of what is to be going on without being confusing then I would start the page over. Tedious but worth it..<br>
Hope you can find a good story because everything's been done already just try to find a different take on the old and make the new.<br>
Hope I didn't frighten any of you away from drawing comics. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/11/02 6:40:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1850.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Need Help With Manga Strip! Just Some Tips.</span><hr size=1> The purpose of a comic is to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> tell a story</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  It's not to showcase anyone's mad art skills.  In the pros' world, yes an artist's name <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> does</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> sell more than the writer's name, but we're not even in the same league.  For you and I, the purpose of a comic is to tell a story. <p><hr noshade size=1><center><font size=1><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/taerx/"> My FreeWebs Home Page</a> (Not a lot there)</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1850.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1850.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1850.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=1850.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.